Fourth-of-July crowd. Their appearance is generally hailed with delight by the 
mariner. Full of fine spirits, they invariably come from the breezy billows to 
windward. They are the lads that always live before the wind. They are 
accounted a lucky omen. If you yourself can withstand three cheers at beholding 
these vivacious fish, then heaven help ye; the spirit of godly gamesomeness is 
